For sale is a 2007 Crestliner 1600 Fish Hawk with a 2007 60hp fuel injected 4 stroke motor and trailer. 

Please be aware, when pricing this on NADA, NADA is giving BASE VALUES FOR STANDARD EQUIPMENT, no options, no cover, no trailer and a 50hp 2 stroke motor ( this has a 60hp fuel injected 4 stroke... ). No, I won't sell the boat for $6250. 

Aluminum hull, single console

Motorguide wireless 12v trolling motor
ProSport 8 Dual bank marine battery charger
2 batteries, one cranking, one deep cycle
AM/FM CD player w/2 speakers.
Full cover with three support poles
Trailer has a swing away tongue. The boat WILL FIT in a building as small as 20' deep with ease.

The seats are all in very good condition, as is the carpet. There are a few small stains in the carpet. There is a slight amount of dock rash on one side. There is no spare tire/rim. I can send detailed photos of all issues. The trailer tires have taken on a goofy wear pattern. I suspect the air pressure was low. There is still plenty of tread. 

This was my father in laws boat. He passed away and we have no use for this. Overall, this is a great boat. It starts and runs perfectly. Top speed is mid 30s according to the speedo. It isn't new, nor is it perfect, but is very presentable and respectable. If it was a pontoon, I'd keep it.

Engine hours are unknown. My father in law has fought cancer the past two years and the boat has sat idle the entire time. 

My wife and I took it out on the water over New Year's weekend at the Lake of the Ozarks and ran it between the 23 and 26mm. It ran perfectly and handled the wind chop better than I expected. 

Do feel free to call or email with any questions you have. I'll happily send detailed photographs (taken in the fall just before I put it in storage ). 

The boat is currently in Sunrise Beach, Mo in inside storage. I live in NE Kansas. Arrangements will need to be made in advance to view the boat. 

Watertests will not happen without proof of funds. That means CASH or CHECK IN HAND. Sorry folks, I'm selling a boat, not giving free boat rides. I'll happily hook it to the garden hose and run the motor for anyone interested.

Scammers, spammers and dopes will not be tolerated.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage Arms/Springfield model 187M in .22
postcontent:
Hi, 
I have a Savage Arms/Springfield model 187M in .22. This is one of the old ones that did not have a serial numbers. I took this in trade a few years ago and until recently it sat in a closet. A couple of months ago, I was going to use her as a Squirrel rifle, put a scope on her and we went to the range. Short of this is that after the first shot, the second round stove pipes because the first is not ejected soon enough. Brought her home, completely stripped her down and nothing really stood out as a problem. I ordered new breech bolt, hammer and extractor plunger springs; installed them and went back to the range. Same problem..I went back and ordered a new extractor, installed it and againsame problem so I put it back in the closet. After doing research on this issue, I did find out that especially in older .22s that were dry-fired; after awhile the firing pin will gouge the chamber causing stove piping. I ordered the .22 Rimfire Chamber Ironing Swage from Brownells for $20.00 plus shipping and thought I had finally got it. No luck and it went back to the closet. Last week, while looking for something in this closet I bumped the rifle and it fell over and the front site landed on my toe. This rifle has to go! I figure if I sell/trade it now for $75.00, Ill only be down a lot of aggravation and a $100.00 or so. Ill sell outright for $75.00 or trade for ammo. (12 gauge, .45, .40, 9mm or .32) Again, this rifle is a nice rifel for its age and very accurate if you only shooting one round at a time. If you can fix it or have experience with these; $75.00 is a steal. Or if you have some extra time on your hands, you could part it out and easily make over $150.00 or so.

I'm selling my gen 4 Glock 22, chambered in .40sw.  It shoots just fine and looks great, I just don't like the recoil of the .40 caliber round.  It's only had 250 rounds fired through it.  The cheapest new one I've found locally is $499, after tax you'd be saving quite a bit buying mine for $500.  It comes with the original factory box and three high capacity (15 round) magazines.  I would take a partial trade for a Glock 17 or 19, preferably with night sights.  If it's a gen 3 or 4 in like new condition, I'll trade even.  If it's been beat up a little but still works, I'll be open to negotiate.  

Call or text: 
REDACTED
I work all times of the day, if I am unable to answer my phone please leave me a message.  I will respond as soon as possible.  Thanks for looking.
